    {
      "section": "Title Page",
      "desc": "the Temporal Log header",
      "passage": "[TEMPORAL LOG // ENTRY_001 // ERA: 14 // NODE: AFTER]",
      "passage_short": "[TEMPORAL LOG // ENTRY_001 // ERA: 14 //",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section": "Title Page",
      "desc": "the system boot warnings",
      "passage": "[SYSTEM BOOT]... CORRUPTED — [LOADING DIRECTIVE]... FAILED — [WARNING: NON-LINEAR NARRATIVE HAZARD] You are not the first version of yourself to read this.",
      "passage_short": "[SYSTEM BOOT]... CORRUPTED — [LOADING DIRECTIVE]... FAILED —",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 34,
          "text": "Rose's voice arrives like someone broke into the book. He doesn't introduce himself. He just starts giving orders. I am writing this in the margin of his first page so he knows I am here.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter I — Time Is an Ocean",
      "desc": "the three questions",
      "passage": "These are the three questions I have never met an Echo who could avoid for long. Every Echo must eventually answer these.",
      "passage_short": "These are the three questions I have never",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 8,
          "text": "Yes Chen, the three questions are also in every TTRPG essay since 2018. Solid framing though.",
          "act": 1,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter I — Time Is an Ocean",
      "desc": "the basic play loop",
      "passage": "1. Play. Navigate through time, encounter situations, make choices. When the outcome is uncertain and the stakes are real...",
      "passage_short": "1. Play. Navigate through time, encounter situations, make",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 9,
          "text": "Game loop is clean: Play, Roll, Respond. About as elegant as Ironsworn. Can teach this to my wife in five minutes.",
          "act": 1,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter II — Excavating Your Echo",
      "desc": "chapter opening",
      "passage": "Before you were Displaced, you had a singular, linear existence. You remember it as \"ordinary\", but that is just what singular and linear feel like when you have never known otherwise.",
      "passage_short": "Before you were Displaced, you had a singular,",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "anchor",
          "size": 5,
          "stage": 3,
          "late": true
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 10,
          "text": "Named my Echo Saul. First Active Memory: smell of rain on hot asphalt. Made me close my eyes for a minute.",
          "act": 1,
          "late": false
        },
        {
          "n": 59,
          "text": "Saul chose the name. I just wrote it down.",
          "act": 5,
          "late": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter II — Excavating Your Echo",
      "desc": "the Temporal Anchor section",
      "passage": "Your Temporal Anchor — An Anchor is Pascal's wager carved into an object. You commit to a person, a place, a promise...",
      "passage_short": "Your Temporal Anchor — An Anchor is Pascal's",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "anchor",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 11,
          "text": "Pascal's wager carved into an object. Good line. I think Chen would have made a good rebbe in another life.",
          "act": 1,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter II — Excavating Your Echo",
      "desc": "the Modes section + Alan's intrusion",
      "passage": "Your Operational Modes — Modes are provisional. Please stop treating them like character classes. [Alan margin:] She's right. They aren't classes.",
      "passage_short": "Your Operational Modes — Modes are provisional. Please",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "momentum",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 12,
          "text": "Wait. Did the book just call me out for treating Modes like classes? I just wrote \"pick DISRUPT for combat builds\" in my notes. OK Alan I see you.",
          "act": 1,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter II — Excavating Your Echo",
      "desc": "Recurring Threads",
      "passage": "Recurring Threads — The timeline bends around people who matter as many times as you let it.",
      "passage_short": "Recurring Threads — The timeline bends around people",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "anchor",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 13,
          "text": "Wrote down the people Saul might choose as Recurring Threads. Ended up writing down mine. My wife is first. Was going to use this for the character. Don't think I will now.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter II — Excavating Your Echo",
      "desc": "the Memory rules section",
      "passage": "Your Five Starting Memories — Memory is the substrate of identity. Cataloguing it is the most important act of preservation you will perform.",
      "passage_short": "Your Five Starting Memories — Memory is the",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "memory",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter III — Opening the Session",
      "desc": "the opening question",
      "passage": "Before you write anything else, write down at least one question your Echo is trying to find out the answer to.",
      "passage_short": "Before you write anything else, write down at",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "momentum",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 14,
          "text": "Saul's question for tonight: what would it have been like to grow up with both parents alive. Wrote it down. Closed the book. Made tea.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter III — Opening the Session",
      "desc": "ending a scene",
      "passage": "A scene ends when: you get what you wanted (success, clean or complicated), you clearly don't get what you wanted...",
      "passage_short": "A scene ends when: you get what you",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "null",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 15,
          "text": "Got into a clean flow tonight. Played three scenes in 45 minutes. Saul stayed at +4 Coherence. This is just resource management with a poetic coat of paint.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter IV — The Resolution Roll",
      "desc": "the resolution roll itself",
      "passage": "When the outcome matters, you roll. Two six-sided dice, plus the relevant Mode, plus your Memory bonus.",
      "passage_short": "When the outcome matters, you roll. Two six-sided",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "momentum",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 16,
          "text": "2d6 + Mode + Memory tag — same math as Forged in the Dark. Comfortable territory. I can play this in my sleep.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter IV — The Resolution Roll",
      "desc": "Structured Correction (Coherence reroll)",
      "passage": "After rolling all four Anomaly Tables, you may spend 1 Coherence to reroll one result.",
      "passage_short": "After rolling all four Anomaly Tables, you may",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "anchor",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 17,
          "text": "Coherence is the only resource that matters. The rest are decoration.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter IV — The Resolution Roll",
      "desc": "Displacement Costs",
      "passage": "Every time you are Displaced — voluntarily or not — you lose Coherence from the wrenching dislocation.",
      "passage_short": "Every time you are Displaced — voluntarily or",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "drift",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter IV — The Resolution Roll",
      "desc": "Shattering reference",
      "passage": "Cause a Shattering deliberately +3",
      "passage_short": "Cause a Shattering deliberately +3",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "collapse",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter IV — The Resolution Roll",
      "desc": "Agent Encounters",
      "passage": "When an Agent appears at Paradox 7-9, they bring an Offer. The form varies — surveillance, interference...",
      "passage_short": "When an Agent appears at Paradox 7-9, they",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "paradox",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 18,
          "text": "The Offers mechanic is mean. Real mean. Saul refused his first one (Loop Authority, of course) and now the Mark stays. I respect the design.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter IV — The Resolution Roll",
      "desc": "Asset Stress",
      "passage": "For each Asset with Stress marked, roll 2d6 + relevant Mode...",
      "passage_short": "For each Asset with Stress marked, roll 2d6",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "burden",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter IV — The Resolution Roll",
      "desc": "Expanded Safety Tools",
      "passage": "Temporal Echoes is a game about loss, memory, and identity erosion. Played at length, it will put you in contact with grief.",
      "passage_short": "Temporal Echoes is a game about loss, memory,",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "null",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 19,
          "text": "Safety tools written by someone who has used them. The \"talk to a person who exists in your life before you pick the book up again\" line is good advice. Going to ignore it because the baby finally went down and this is my window.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter V — Architecture of Self",
      "desc": "chapter opening",
      "passage": "When memory fails, identity collapses. Collapses start small. First, the Echo can't remember...",
      "passage_short": "When memory fails, identity collapses. Collapses start small.",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 20,
          "text": "Spent an hour today looking for an old photograph of my zayde. Wanted to see if it felt like an Anchor. It did. Heavier than a piece of paper should be.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter V — Architecture of Self",
      "desc": "Lost Memories",
      "passage": "Lost Memories — Gone from conscious mind. No bonus. They leave Scars — narrative consequences, behavioral changes, the shape of what was.",
      "passage_short": "Lost Memories — Gone from conscious mind. No",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "collapse",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 21,
          "text": "Rolled a 6. Saul lost the memory of his mother's voice. I tried to hum the lullaby I wrote in the margins three weeks ago. Couldn't remember the melody.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter V — Architecture of Self",
      "desc": "the Mutation table",
      "passage": "When you gain a Mutation — from Paradox Breach, from a Faction trade, from a Crisis outcome that specifies it — choose one...",
      "passage_short": "When you gain a Mutation — from Paradox",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "drift",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 22,
          "text": "This table is harder to read than the rest of the chapter. Like the book doesn't want me to look directly at it. Will note that and move on.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter V — Architecture of Self",
      "desc": "Memory restoration on 12+",
      "passage": "12+ Against all odds, it returns. The Memory enters an Active slot...",
      "passage_short": "12+ Against all odds, it returns. The Memory",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "ripple",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 23,
          "text": "Started noticing little circle marks in Chen's margins next to certain mechanical terms. They look like physics notation. There's a key in Appendix A. Saving it for later.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter V — Architecture of Self",
      "desc": "Chen's confession at chapter end",
      "passage": "I followed every procedure. Every rule. Every preservation protocol in Chen's manual. I maintained Coherence above +5 for...",
      "passage_short": "I followed every procedure. Every rule. Every preservation",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "null",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 24,
          "text": "This page is in Chen's voice but it reads like a confession. She did everything right and lost everything anyway. The Chronicle is becoming more than a journal. I am writing things in here I have never told anyone.",
          "act": 2,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VI — Crisis Management",
      "desc": "Manifestation phase",
      "passage": "Crises come in three phases. Manifestation is the moment you recognize what is happening. Your chest tightening, the room...",
      "passage_short": "Crises come in three phases. Manifestation is the",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 25,
          "text": "Did not open this book today. Found it open on my desk. The ink in the margins on this page is a different color — a deep, bruised purple. Still wet to the touch.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VI — Crisis Management",
      "desc": "Compound Crisis procedure",
      "passage": "Roll on the Timeline Shifts Oracle to determine how reality changes.",
      "passage_short": "Roll on the Timeline Shifts Oracle to determine",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "collapse",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 26,
          "text": "Rolled Saul's first Compound Crisis. Cleared it on the dice. Walked to the kitchen and forgot why for a full minute. The dice cleared it. Not sure I did.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VI — Crisis Management",
      "desc": "the four Faction Interventions — THE VISUAL CENTERPIECE",
      "passage": "CHURCH INTERVENTION — Templars arrive attempting capture for ritual use. AUTHORITY INTERVENTION — Clone Loop. They're going to convince you you've done this before. CHRONOCLAST INTERVENTION — They don't try to recruit you, they try to detonate you. SCIONFALL INTERVENTION — A Herald manifests.",
      "passage_short": "CHURCH INTERVENTION — Templars arrive attempting capture for",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 27,
          "text": "Apikoros. Looked the word up. Hebrew for heretic. The one my rebbe used for anyone who said Hashem wasn't watching. Rose is an apikoros. He is also infecting me.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VI — Crisis Management",
      "desc": "Results on a Compound Crisis",
      "passage": "12+ Full stabilization. Both Crises end.",
      "passage_short": "12+ Full stabilization. Both Crises end.",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VII — Holding Actions",
      "desc": "the Holding Action mechanic",
      "passage": "Once per session, when you would suffer a consequence you cannot afford to bear in this scene, you may declare a Holding Action.",
      "passage_short": "Once per session, when you would suffer a",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "burden",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 28,
          "text": "The Holding Action is the most honest mechanic in the book. You can refuse the consequence once. Once. Then the bill comes due. I have used it twice this week in real life.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VII — Holding Actions",
      "desc": "Anchor Strength Loss Triggers",
      "passage": "Outside of the Reinforce Anchor move, your Anchor Strength can decrease when: An Identity...",
      "passage_short": "Outside of the Reinforce Anchor move, your Anchor",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VII — Holding Actions",
      "desc": "Asset damage",
      "passage": "Assets take damage from critical failures when using them, high Paradox effects, direct attacks, environmental hazards...",
      "passage_short": "Assets take damage from critical failures when using",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "burden",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 29,
          "text": "My watch stopped today. Not the battery. The hands melted into the face. Checked the sheet — Saul's Asset Stress is maxed. The math knew before I did.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VIII — Campaign Structures",
      "desc": "Campaign Structures",
      "passage": "Temporal Echoes supports several campaign structures. They're not mutually exclusive — your campaign...",
      "passage_short": "Temporal Echoes supports several campaign structures. They're not",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "recursion",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 30,
          "text": "Campaign structures are good. Not going to use them. Saul and I are on the One True Run now. There is no other version of this campaign.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Chapter VIII — Campaign Structures",
      "desc": "Faction Escalation",
      "passage": "Evolving Threats — Faction Escalation — As Paradox rises, Faction interference increases: Shadow (0-3) — unaware of you. Flux...",
      "passage_short": "Evolving Threats — Faction Escalation — As Paradox",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "ripple",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 31,
          "text": "Saw a man in a grey suit on Hennepin standing perfectly still. Looked exactly like the Loop Authority sketch on page 54. No one else seemed to see him. My heart skipped a beat but I kept walking. I have a baby. I do not have time for hallucinations.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Interlude — Playing Both / A Note from the Journalist",
      "desc": "the Journalist opening",
      "passage": "INTERLUDE — Playing Both — A NOTE FROM THE JOURNALIST",
      "passage_short": "INTERLUDE — Playing Both — A NOTE FROM",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 32,
          "text": "Wait. There is a third voice now. A \"Journalist.\" Did Chen write this? Did Rose? Why does it feel like neither. Why does it feel like me.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "Interlude — Playing Both / A Note from the Journalist",
      "desc": "the Journalist's premise",
      "passage": "So. You finished Chen's book. Or you skipped to here, which is allowed, but you should know that some of what follows would be incomprehensible if you hadn't.",
      "passage_short": "So. You finished Chen's book. Or you skipped",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 33,
          "text": "He says reading both books changes the meaning of both. He is the only one in this manuscript who is telling me the truth.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "ENTRY_001 — After the Tutorial",
      "desc": "the 1944 reveal",
      "passage": "You want to know how I learned this. 2044. Four of us in a building that was already coming down. I had ninety seconds to...",
      "passage_short": "You want to know how I learned this.",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 35,
          "text": "1944. The building. Four people. I have only been reading for six weeks and I already know this story by its silhouette. The book is teaching me its own grammer.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "ENTRY_001 — After the Tutorial",
      "desc": "The Real Situation",
      "passage": "THE REAL SITUATION — By now you've noticed. Every time you hold onto who you were, it costs more than it should.",
      "passage_short": "THE REAL SITUATION — By now you've noticed.",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "drift",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 36,
          "text": "Drew a small circle with a line through it in the margin without thinking about it. Looked at it. My handwriting matches Chen's exactly.",
          "act": 3,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "ENTRY_002 — Calibration",
      "desc": "walking weapon",
      "passage": "Stop pretending you're still human. You are a walking weapon. A living bomb on causality and a bona fide wound in space-time.",
      "passage_short": "Stop pretending you're still human. You are a",
      "glyphs": [],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 37,
          "text": "Rose talks like he has been waiting for me specifically. He has not. He has been waiting for whoever was next.",
          "act": 4,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "ENTRY_002 — Calibration",
      "desc": "the Infectious trait",
      "passage": "Infectious — When you interact with an NPC, you may choose to transfer 1 point of your Paradox to them. Reduce your Paradox...",
      "passage_short": "Infectious — When you interact with an NPC,",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "ripple",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "n": 38,
          "text": "Saul and I have both been Marked. Cannot tell which of us anymore. Maybe this is what Chen meant by Wave Coherence.",
          "act": 4,
          "late": false
        },
        {
          "n": 39,
          "text": "Tried the Infectious move on the baby this morning. Touched his head and tried to transfer a point. Nothing happened. Not sure if that is good news.",
          "act": 4,
          "late": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "ENTRY_002 — Calibration",
      "desc": "Asset States",
      "passage": "ASSET STATES (EMIT) — Every Asset in emiT exists in one of three states. Track this on your sheet. Clean — The Asset functions...",
      "passage_short": "ASSET STATES (EMIT) — Every Asset in emiT",
      "glyphs": [
        {
          "glyph": "burden",
          "size": 6,
          "stage": 0,
          "late": false
